headline: Google- and Dell-Backed SingleStore Sold to Vector Capital
summary: Terms of the deal weren’t disclosed in a statement Wednesday that confirmed an earlier Bloomberg News report.  Vector and its co-investors are investing about $500 million in equity in SingleStore, according to people familiar with the matter who asked not to be identified because the matter is private.

headline: Oracle's AI growth: Why another name could see similar gains
summary: Oracle (ORCL) stock is skyrocketing after the company reported strong artificial intelligence (AI) backorders. Visible Alpha head of TMT research Melissa Otto joins Opening Bid with Yahoo Finance Head of News Myles Udland to discuss the stock's rally and to share one other name she says could see similar AI-related growth later in the year. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.
